Today I am excited to announce a new addition: the Asianometry ( https://as=
ianometry.passport.online/member/ ) newsletter and podcast, by Jon Yu.

Asianometry is one of the best tech YouTube channels in existence ( https:/=
/www.youtube.com/@Asianometry ) , with over 768,000 subscribers. Jon produc=
es in-depth videos explaining every aspect of technology, with a particular=
 expertise in semiconductors. To give you an idea of Jon's depth, he has ma=
de 31 videos about TSMC alone ( https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=3DPLK=
txx9TnH76SRC7ZbOu2Nsg5mC72fy-GZ ). His semiconductor course ( https://www.y=
outube.com/playlist?list=3DPLKtxx9TnH76QY5FjmO3NaUkVJvTPN9Vmg ) includes 30=
 videos covering everything from designing chips ( https://www.youtube.com/=
watch?v=3Dihz2WY-E2C8&list=3DPLKtxx9TnH76QY5FjmO3NaUkVJvTPN9Vmg&index=3D2&p=
p=3DiAQB ) to how ASML builds EUV machines ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?=
v=3DjJIO7aRXUCg&list=3DPLKtxx9TnH76QY5FjmO3NaUkVJvTPN9Vmg&index=3D4&pp=3DiA=
QB ) to Moore's Law ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3DnRJgvX6P8dI&list=3D=
PLKtxx9TnH76QY5FjmO3NaUkVJvTPN9Vmg&index=3D20&pp=3DiAQB ). His video on the=
 end of Dennard's Law is a particular standout:

( https://www.youtube.com/embed/7p8ZeSbblec?si=3D7lsVdhKiD0Nu9QRe )

Jon is about more than semiconductors though: he's made videos about other =
tech topics like The Tragedy of Compaq ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3D=
47ovT_hYlt8&list=3DPLKtxx9TnH76RKmJlFIfs7NumNp1RPNIQv&index=3D4&pp=3DiAQB )=
 , and non-tech topics like Japanese Whisky ( https://www.youtube.com/watch=
?v=3D19l7WkkwYi8&list=3DPLKtxx9TnH76RKmJlFIfs7NumNp1RPNIQv&index=3D5&pp=3Di=
AQB ) and Taiwan convenience stores ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3DvKB=
Y-MJFJ4A&list=3DPLKtxx9TnH76RKmJlFIfs7NumNp1RPNIQv&index=3D6&pp=3DiAQB ). I=
n short, Jon is an intensely curious person who does his research, and we a=
re blessed that he puts in the work to share what he learns.

I am blessed most of all, however. Over the last year Jon has been making S=
tratechery Articles into video essays ( https://www.youtube.com/@Stratecher=
y ) and cutting clips for Sharp Tech ( https://www.youtube.com/@SharpTechPo=
dcast ) ; he did a great job with one of my favorite articles of 2024:

( https://www.youtube.com/embed/3cgjWHzFdj4?si=3DwzdTd1X144pDIwcJ )

And now, starting today, Stratechery Plus subscribers can get exclusive acc=
ess to Asianometry's content in newsletter and podcast form. The Asianometr=
y YouTube Channel ( https://www.youtube.com/@Asianometry ) will remain free=
 and Jon's primary focus, but from now on all of his content will be simult=
aneously released as a transcript and podcast. Stratechery Plus subscribers=
 can head over to the new Asianometry Passport site ( https://asianometry.p=
assport.online/member/ ) to subscribe to his emails, or to add the podcast =
feed to your favorite podcast player.

And, of course, subscribe to Jon's YouTube channel ( https://www.youtube.co=
m/@Asianometry/ ) , along with Stratechery Plus ( https://stratechery.passp=
ort.online/member/plan/4ycW4SE71Cy6ryrijywbTG ).

